  "user_intent_preservation": {
    "original_goal": "Migrate the TC387 3-phase inverter (GTM TOM + EVADC) to TC4D7 using eGTM ATOM and TMADC on KIT_A3G_TC4D7_LITE.",
    "functional_behavior": "Produce 3-phase complementary, center-aligned PWM at 20 kHz on EGTM ATOM0 Cluster 0 CH0–2 with CDTM/DTM deadtime = 1.0 µs (rise/fall), initial duties U/V/W = 25%/50%/75%. Use ATOM0 C0 CH3 as the ADC trigger (edge-aligned, 50% duty, falling edge) and also output it on P33.0. Remap PWM outputs to P20.8–P20.13 (U: P20.8/P20.9, V: P20.10/P20.11, W: P20.12/P20.13). Configure LED on P03.9 low-active. Replace IfxScuWdt with IfxWtu. Move duty updates to main loop at 500 ms. Configure TMADC0 with 5 channels, all triggered from ATOM0 C0 CH3.",
    "technical_approach": "Use unified high-level IfxEgtm_Pwm for multi-channel ATOM PWM with center alignment and hardware deadtime via IfxEgtm_Dtm. Route ATOM0 C0 CH3 trigger to TMADC0 using IfxEgtm_Trigger_trigToAdc and also map CH3 to P33.0 using IfxEgtm_PinMap. Initialize TMADC0 and channels with IfxAdc_Tmadc. Replace watchdog APIs with IfxWtu. GPIO with IfxPort remains unchanged."
  },
